{it}The English{/it} is the most commonly used collective term for the people of England. {it}Englander{/it} and {it}Englisher{/it} refer to a native or inhabitant of England, but especially when the gender is known, {it}Englishman{/it} and {it}Englishwoman{/it} are much more commonly used.
